{
  "texts": [
    "Maintaining any inaccuracy that arises throughout the many layers and timeframes is the primary goal of the LSTM (Nicholson and Gibson, 2018).",
    "The hidden layer has cells with three gates: an input, an output, and a forget gate.",
    "These gates store data and control information flow to predict the network's production (Chen et al., 2018).",
    "This one cell helps the model decide what to store and when to change information through the gates.",
    "GRUs have two gates: an update gate and a reset gate."
  ]
}